summary: Hiiii, thoughts on killing eve?
question: Hiiii, thoughts on killing eve?
answer:
Hiii, we have finished season one but we haven’t watched season two yet and while I really do want to watch it (and we will), I am a bit soured on the whole thing because of the relentless queerbaiting. Which it clearly is.

I am beyond, BEYOND tired of media being sold to lesbians (& the LGBT community in general, really, but man it happens to lesbians a whole fucking lot) and being sold something in a certain way - a very calculated way, in Killing Eve’s case - only to be told that no, the way we read it was wrong, and it’s all in our heads, and we’re seeing things that aren’t there.

That show was marketed to lesbians. For lesbians. With its suggestive photoshoots of Sandra and Jodie, with its “sorry baby x” and “have you seen my girlfriend?”, with its characters admitting that they masturbate to each other, and love each other, and are attracted to each other - to have all of those things be written off, and not actual mean ANYTHING, and to actually have it thrown in our faces and be told “they aren’t lesbians, that would be the cliche thing to do” is fucking infuriating.

They want us to consume their media, but they do not want us to be in their media. I’m tired, dude.
